WEBVTT

00:36.266 --> 00:39.060
WE ARE ALL TRYING HERE

00:45.275 --> 00:47.527
Dong-man, it's time to give up.

00:47.610 --> 00:49.821
How long will you pursue something
that's not working?

00:49.904 --> 00:51.489
If you'd gritted your teeth
and gone all in,

00:51.573 --> 00:53.116
you would've made it in ten years.

00:53.199 --> 00:55.618
But you just let 20 years slip by,

00:55.702 --> 00:58.496
just eating and shitting repeatedly.

00:59.664 --> 01:01.207
Instead of holding onto
what won't work out

01:01.291 --> 01:02.917
and getting jealous
of other people's success,

01:03.001 --> 01:04.919
start living more constructively

01:05.003 --> 01:06.629
and productively from now on.

01:09.424 --> 01:11.593
Why the hell does my life
have to please you, sir?

01:16.472 --> 01:18.600
You crazy bastard! What are you doing?

01:41.956 --> 01:44.626
Hey, Dong-man!

01:47.378 --> 01:49.380
Hwang Dong-man!

01:54.552 --> 01:56.387
Hey, Dong-man!

01:58.514 --> 02:00.433
Hwang Dong-man!

02:07.232 --> 02:08.316
I'm here!

02:10.109 --> 02:11.444
I'm here!

02:15.823 --> 02:17.951
Hey, Dong-man!

02:20.161 --> 02:22.747
Hwang Dong-man!

02:34.008 --> 02:35.510
Mr. Hwang Dong-man, are you in there?

02:38.346 --> 02:39.847
We're from the Hyoeun Precinct.

02:39.931 --> 02:41.516
Mr. Hwang Dong-man?

02:43.017 --> 02:44.352
Mr. Hwang Dong-man?

02:51.943 --> 02:53.111
Excuse me.

02:53.736 --> 02:54.821
Are you Mr. Hwang Dong-man?

02:55.488 --> 02:56.572
Yes, how can I help you?

02:57.991 --> 02:59.283
Do you live alone?

03:00.034 --> 03:01.035
No.

03:03.329 --> 03:06.040
-Oh, my older brother
-Yes?

03:06.124 --> 03:09.419
works in the countryside,
so he comes and goes.

03:10.003 --> 03:12.213
Then who keeps shouting for you?

03:13.339 --> 03:14.841
-Sorry?
-Huh?

03:17.135 --> 03:20.013
Oh, you see, we received a complaint.

03:20.096 --> 03:23.057
They said someone calls out your name
at all hours of the day,

03:23.141 --> 03:25.393
so they can't get any sleep.

03:27.812 --> 03:30.314
The only Hwang Dong-man
who lives in this area

03:30.398 --> 03:33.192
happens to be you, Mr. Hwang Dong-man.

03:34.736 --> 03:36.112
So who keeps calling for you?

03:39.782 --> 03:41.784
-My brother…
-What about him?

03:49.917 --> 03:54.047
He should call you on his phone instead.

03:54.672 --> 03:58.009
Please tell him to stop shouting for you
because we're getting complaints.

03:58.593 --> 04:01.429
And please open the door quickly
when we call for you.

04:01.512 --> 04:02.597
-Okay.
-All right.

04:06.893 --> 04:08.144
WE SELL GIMBAP

04:08.227 --> 04:10.063
Two rolls of gimbap, please.

04:10.146 --> 04:11.272
Here you go.

04:12.899 --> 04:14.275
-Thank you.
-Have a good day.

04:14.359 --> 04:15.818
Goodbye.

04:26.120 --> 04:28.122
Does Jae-yeong eat braised black beans?

04:29.165 --> 04:31.376
If he says he doesn't, bring it back.

05:15.044 --> 05:17.046
Are you crazy? Why would I beat him up?

05:17.630 --> 05:19.424
I didn't even touch him.

05:19.507 --> 05:20.341
Look.

05:20.425 --> 05:21.509
He was sitting right here,

05:22.844 --> 05:25.596
fidgeting like this,
before he suddenly jumped up

05:25.680 --> 05:27.306
and tried to grab me by the collar.

05:27.390 --> 05:29.892
I don't know if the idiot
tripped over his own feet,

05:29.976 --> 05:31.894
but he reached out like this…

05:34.313 --> 05:35.231
then fell on his face.

05:39.652 --> 05:41.487
Did I touch you at all?

05:42.405 --> 05:43.447
Jeez.

05:44.407 --> 05:46.075
It takes real talent to do that.

05:47.493 --> 05:50.454
I mean, all he had to do
was slide across and…

05:51.080 --> 05:53.040
Is this so hard? Is it?

05:54.125 --> 05:55.877
He's so frustrating.

05:58.296 --> 06:01.007
Then how did he get hurt?
I heard he got a cast.

06:01.757 --> 06:03.593
He probably got drunk and fell on his ass.

06:05.011 --> 06:06.387
I hear the Eight Club is meeting today.

06:07.471 --> 06:08.514
Or should I say the Seven Club?

06:10.099 --> 06:11.976
Anyway, tell Director Park Yeong-su

06:12.059 --> 06:14.228
that I didn't
go for Hwang Dong-man's jugular

06:14.312 --> 06:16.314
to play the hero or something.

06:16.397 --> 06:18.357
I feel crappy about this too.

06:19.275 --> 06:21.903
But since you fine folks

06:22.653 --> 06:25.031
couldn't stand to get your hands dirty,

06:25.531 --> 06:27.325
I did the dirty work for you

06:27.992 --> 06:30.703
because I'm just a lowborn peasant.

06:33.247 --> 06:35.708
You're all so noble, aren't you?

07:01.025 --> 07:03.653
WEATHER MAKER
BY HWANG DONG-MAN

07:19.669 --> 07:22.046
1F: AGIT
2F: KOPARK FILM PRODUCTION

07:22.630 --> 07:24.298
Don't you think Mr. Choi crossed the line?

07:25.007 --> 07:28.302
Who does he think he is,
telling one of us to quit?

07:29.428 --> 07:30.638
We handle our own business.

07:30.721 --> 07:32.098
Who among us will do it?

07:34.100 --> 07:35.560
Think this through, Yeong-su.

07:37.645 --> 07:40.231
Hwang Dong-man
needs to leave this industry.

07:41.274 --> 07:42.817
There's no point staying
because he won't make it.

07:44.360 --> 07:48.030
It's better that he quits
than to go around stirring shit up.

07:48.656 --> 07:49.991
Look at what happened yesterday.

07:50.825 --> 07:52.785
After getting humiliated by Mr. Choi,

07:52.868 --> 07:55.371
you'd think he'd go off the grid
and return with a masterpiece.

07:55.454 --> 07:57.665
Or just grit his teeth
and leave this industry!

07:58.249 --> 08:01.168
Instead, he sent over 100 messages
in our group chat overnight,

08:01.877 --> 08:04.380
complimenting Director Kim's movie,

08:04.463 --> 08:06.716
knowing it's competing
for screens with my movie.

08:06.799 --> 08:07.800
He knows I'm in the group chat.

08:07.883 --> 08:09.302
He's a total lunatic!

08:11.012 --> 08:12.930
It drives him insane
when someone does well.

08:13.431 --> 08:16.225
But he's ecstatic when someone fails.

08:16.809 --> 08:17.810
What an asshole.

08:18.894 --> 08:22.189
When my second movie tanked
right after it was released,

08:23.774 --> 08:26.277
he suddenly sent me a private message,

08:26.360 --> 08:28.321
telling me to keep my chin up
and got me coffee.

08:28.404 --> 08:29.655
Acting all nice and caring.

08:30.573 --> 08:31.907
I felt like shit.

08:33.200 --> 08:35.161
That's the kind of person
Hwang Dong-man is.

08:35.244 --> 08:38.080
There are only two things he does all day.

08:38.164 --> 08:40.082
Dying from jealousy
when someone does well,

08:40.166 --> 08:42.627
and dying from happiness
when he sees someone fail.

08:45.129 --> 08:46.213
Well, I can't say

08:47.131 --> 08:49.258
that I've never felt that way myself.

08:49.342 --> 08:52.261
Of course, everyone feels that way!

08:52.345 --> 08:55.640
But nobody goes as far as Hwang Dong-man!

08:55.723 --> 08:58.017
A normal person would stop and think,

08:58.100 --> 08:59.894
"I'm acting petty. I shouldn't do that."

08:59.977 --> 09:02.229
But that bastard just keeps going!

09:02.313 --> 09:04.523
He's got no self-control!

09:05.024 --> 09:07.943
He won't stop
until we all become failures like him.

09:13.324 --> 09:15.159
It's not just actors
who have to be careful.

09:16.160 --> 09:17.703
We have to be careful too.

09:18.287 --> 09:21.123
Being associated with Hwang Dong-man
is just asking for trouble.

09:21.207 --> 09:23.709
People who are bitter
about their own failures drag others down.

09:23.793 --> 09:24.710
You know what I mean.

09:25.252 --> 09:27.713
He ruins everything wherever he goes.

09:28.214 --> 09:30.549
We're just tossing out a rotten tangerine.

09:30.633 --> 09:33.052
Hwang Dong-man is rotten to the core!

09:33.135 --> 09:35.054
If we leave him be,
the rest of us will rot too!

09:35.137 --> 09:36.889
Damn it, I think I'm already rotting.

09:41.852 --> 09:44.480
But to end
a 20-year relationship like this…

09:46.816 --> 09:48.317
It doesn't sit right with me.

09:48.401 --> 09:50.236
Oh, come on. Stop being so dramatic!

09:50.319 --> 09:52.446
Who cares if it's been 20 years?

09:53.364 --> 09:56.617
People cut family ties these days.
Knowing someone for years isn't important!

09:57.993 --> 10:00.663
They say as you get older,
you have to sort out your relationships.

10:00.746 --> 10:02.456
That's the key to a long and healthy life.

10:02.540 --> 10:03.833
I've been feeling that lately!

10:05.292 --> 10:06.293
Yeong-su.

10:07.002 --> 10:09.463
There's nothing to feel guilty about.

10:11.298 --> 10:13.676
We're not doing anything terrible.

10:15.678 --> 10:17.471
Would you rather we all go down with him?

10:17.555 --> 10:19.098
What about The Eight Club?

10:20.141 --> 10:21.016
Tell me.

10:22.351 --> 10:23.686
Is this the end?

10:23.769 --> 10:25.563
Stop going on about The Eight Club!

10:28.607 --> 10:31.902
We're not a bunch of kids
who formed a club to lean on each other.

10:32.695 --> 10:35.281
Sure, we hung out as a group
when we were younger.

10:35.364 --> 10:40.411
But we don't need to do that anymore
because we can handle ourselves!

10:45.666 --> 10:46.917
Whatever.

10:47.001 --> 10:49.545
I don't care if you keep seeing him
or not, but I'm out.

10:50.171 --> 10:53.507
I'm leaving the group chat,
and I'm done with The Eight Club.

10:53.591 --> 10:55.468
You can become The Seven Club or whatever.

10:56.051 --> 10:57.178
And Hye-jin.

10:57.261 --> 10:58.387
Shut this place down.

10:59.346 --> 11:02.808
I can't stand the sight of that bastard
hanging around here all the time.

11:03.392 --> 11:05.644
Hey, you're at fault too.

11:05.728 --> 11:08.773
You know how much
Dong-man stresses us out,

11:08.856 --> 11:11.025
but you always hold a bottle for him here.

11:11.525 --> 11:14.737
I heard you even call in to check
if he's run out of booze.

11:19.408 --> 11:21.911
You feel sorry for him, but not for me?

11:21.994 --> 11:25.080
He spent the whole night
showering praise on someone else's movie.

11:25.164 --> 11:27.082
Did you even think about
how that made me feel?

11:28.876 --> 11:29.835
Tell me, Lee Jun-hwan.

11:31.337 --> 11:32.254
What about me?

11:33.756 --> 11:34.965
Don't you feel sorry for me?

11:38.344 --> 11:39.345
I do.

11:41.472 --> 11:43.516
I mean, I feel sorry for all of us.

11:44.475 --> 11:46.644
This guy has zero standards.

11:47.144 --> 11:49.438
He'll take anyone who likes him,
even with women.

11:49.522 --> 11:51.315
He has no taste in people whatsoever.

11:52.608 --> 11:53.567
Whatever.

11:55.236 --> 11:56.403
I've said my piece.

11:57.738 --> 11:58.614
I am

11:59.490 --> 12:00.574
leaving The Eight Club.

12:01.909 --> 12:03.410
I'm leaving the group chat too.

12:04.453 --> 12:06.455
Don't invite me anywhere Dong-man will be.

12:06.539 --> 12:07.414
That's it.

12:08.541 --> 12:09.542
I'm done.

12:10.501 --> 12:11.418
The end.

12:18.717 --> 12:20.219
God, that bastard's here again.

12:22.137 --> 12:23.055
That little…

12:27.726 --> 12:28.769
I'm ending this today.

12:28.852 --> 12:30.354
Come on, Gyeong-se.

12:30.437 --> 12:31.897
Not today, all right?

12:32.523 --> 12:34.733
It hasn't been long
since Mr. Choi came down hard on him.

12:34.817 --> 12:36.235
Not today, Gyeong-se.

12:36.318 --> 12:37.152
I'm sorry.

12:38.320 --> 12:39.488
-I'm leaving.
-Where are you…

12:39.572 --> 12:41.407
-That little bastard.
-Gyeong-se!

12:42.449 --> 12:43.993
You're the problem.

12:44.076 --> 12:45.869
Let's go eat!

12:46.495 --> 12:48.455
-Where are you going?
-I have to go home.

12:50.332 --> 12:52.042
What's wrong with your arm?

12:52.126 --> 12:53.252
How did you get hurt?

12:54.753 --> 12:55.963
It's broken.

12:56.046 --> 12:57.256
But it'll heal.

12:57.339 --> 12:59.717
I'm hungry. Let's go eat.

13:00.217 --> 13:01.176
I want some meat.

13:01.260 --> 13:03.137
Look at the time. We've already eaten.

13:03.220 --> 13:04.346
We have steak, right?

13:04.430 --> 13:05.472
-Cook him one.
-Okay.

13:15.065 --> 13:16.108
What's that?

13:16.191 --> 13:17.651
Is that special effects makeup?

13:18.652 --> 13:19.987
You said you were leaving. Go.

13:21.030 --> 13:22.197
Let's call it a night.

13:22.281 --> 13:23.198
Right, let's go.

13:24.450 --> 13:25.409
Did you punch him?

13:26.827 --> 13:28.495
How can someone's forehead

13:29.330 --> 13:30.956
get so purple?

13:31.040 --> 13:32.791
-I thought you were leaving.
-Want to hear

13:32.875 --> 13:34.293
how this happened?

13:34.376 --> 13:35.252
Yeah.

13:40.090 --> 13:42.009
Don't point your finger at me!

13:42.092 --> 13:43.010
Hey!

13:45.763 --> 13:47.348
He hit it really hard.

13:51.644 --> 13:53.854
There are two kinds of people
in the world.

13:54.355 --> 13:56.732
Those who dedicate themselves
to their own path,

13:58.275 --> 14:01.236
and those who dedicate themselves
to tearing others down.

14:06.825 --> 14:07.660
Right. So?

14:13.624 --> 14:15.417
I said there are two kinds of people
in the world.

14:15.501 --> 14:16.585
Yeah, I heard you.

14:17.628 --> 14:19.546
"Those who dedicate themselves
to their own path,

14:20.172 --> 14:23.133
and those who dedicate themselves
to tearing others down."

14:23.217 --> 14:26.011
The people who dedicate themselves
to tearing others down…

14:28.764 --> 14:30.307
I'm talking to you, you bastard!

14:30.391 --> 14:32.601
-Get out of my way. Hey.
-No, wait.

14:32.685 --> 14:33.519
I'm talking to you!

14:33.602 --> 14:34.812
-Let me go.
-Grab him.

14:34.895 --> 14:36.188
I was talking to you!

14:36.271 --> 14:37.439
I was talking!

14:37.523 --> 14:38.691
-That damn phone.
-Stop it.

14:38.774 --> 14:40.109
-I was talking to you!
-Calm down.

14:40.192 --> 14:41.986
-Give me your phone.
-Calm down.

14:42.069 --> 14:43.404
I was talking to you!

14:43.487 --> 14:44.571
Let go of me.

14:50.494 --> 14:52.454
Can I finish what I was saying?

14:56.041 --> 14:57.042
Ready.

14:57.793 --> 14:58.669
Action.

15:01.630 --> 15:03.507
There are two kinds of people
in the world.

15:04.466 --> 15:06.635
Those who dedicate themselves
to their own path,

15:07.136 --> 15:09.805
and those who dedicate themselves
to tearing others down.

15:10.764 --> 15:12.057
Do you know why

15:13.225 --> 15:15.894
the latter will never stop
tearing others down?

15:16.854 --> 15:20.149
Because it's the only way

15:21.942 --> 15:23.485
they can feel superior to everyone else.

15:25.529 --> 15:27.448
That really hits hard, doesn't it?

15:27.531 --> 15:31.577
I was going to crush
that bastard's pride today.

15:34.204 --> 15:35.372
Go again. Get it all out.

15:35.914 --> 15:36.749
Ready.

15:37.207 --> 15:38.083
Action!

15:38.959 --> 15:41.003
There are two kinds of people
in the world.

15:41.086 --> 15:43.297
Those who dedicate themselves
to their own path,

15:43.380 --> 15:46.842
and those who dedicate themselves
to tearing others down.

15:56.393 --> 15:57.853
Nothing cheers you up like meat.

16:03.233 --> 16:05.027
Wine glasses break easily. Take it away.

16:05.903 --> 16:08.030
-Just pour it in this.
-Don't worry.

16:08.614 --> 16:09.531
It's okay if it breaks.

16:14.411 --> 16:17.498
I was feeling like crap,

16:17.581 --> 16:21.126
so I spent all day watching movies
to get a mood-lifting massage.

16:23.003 --> 16:26.381
These people do nothing but make films,
but that's the best they can do?

16:26.465 --> 16:28.592
In my opinion, all Korean film producers

16:28.675 --> 16:31.095
need to take a hard look at themselves.

16:31.178 --> 16:33.680
This is a must
for people in the film industry.

16:33.764 --> 16:37.309
They should watch their own work
and see how they actually feel.

16:37.392 --> 16:40.062
All I get is "bored, bored, bored, bored,
annoyed, annoyed, annoyed,

16:40.145 --> 16:43.232
dull, dull, dull, dull, annoyed, annoyed,
annoyed, annoyed, annoyed."

16:53.492 --> 16:54.993
Why do you think
it's not working out for you?

16:57.079 --> 16:59.957
People crave power.

17:00.624 --> 17:02.751
I hate it when people say "heal the soul"!

17:02.835 --> 17:04.837
I just need something to lift my mood!

17:04.920 --> 17:06.672
What's there to life? Nothing!

17:06.755 --> 17:08.465
But we can't just die either,

17:08.549 --> 17:10.425
so we need enough strength
to get through the day!

17:10.509 --> 17:13.887
That's why people watch movies
and eat good food!

17:13.971 --> 17:17.307
That's why people go on trips,
fall in love, have sex,

17:17.391 --> 17:19.309
get hammered all night long,

17:19.393 --> 17:21.478
and yell at the top of our lungs!

17:21.562 --> 17:23.397
Fuck!

17:36.243 --> 17:38.370
Don't think. Just listen.

17:38.954 --> 17:41.707
Don't think about what to say back
and just listen.

17:42.875 --> 17:45.002
For the next 3 minutes and 27 seconds,

17:45.085 --> 17:46.420
you're not allowed to say a word.

17:47.337 --> 17:49.214
Not a single word until you leave,

17:49.923 --> 17:51.592
so listen up.

17:56.430 --> 17:57.264
You're right.

17:57.931 --> 17:59.933
Life is about
getting mood-lifting massages.

18:01.059 --> 18:03.020
How can I lift my mood?

18:03.103 --> 18:04.563
I work my ass off to make money

18:04.646 --> 18:07.107
and buy clothes, get my nails done,
and do my hair.

18:08.483 --> 18:09.568
But you know what?

18:10.360 --> 18:11.862
You always ruin my mood.

18:13.572 --> 18:15.199
I want the time I spend with friends

18:15.282 --> 18:18.827
to be a chance to show
my easygoing, generous side.

18:18.911 --> 18:20.037
But whenever I see you,

18:20.954 --> 18:23.582
I just end up feeling bitter and drained.

18:25.500 --> 18:28.754
You know that you can't have
a proper conversation with people, right?

18:30.047 --> 18:31.048
Or that you refuse to.

18:36.929 --> 18:38.388
-But I do.
-Shut up.

18:38.472 --> 18:39.765
You just talk nonstop.

18:45.479 --> 18:46.313
That's not true.

18:46.897 --> 18:48.190
Talking to you is impossible,

18:48.273 --> 18:49.399
and you talk nonstop.

18:49.483 --> 18:50.525
And you're all over the place.

18:50.609 --> 18:51.777
And you piss everyone off.

18:53.153 --> 18:54.988
I plan to live to 100,

18:55.072 --> 18:57.199
so I don't want any more stress
because of you.

18:58.742 --> 18:59.868
So as of today,

19:00.577 --> 19:02.079
I'm cutting ties with you.

19:03.080 --> 19:05.040
I created this place to unwind,

19:05.123 --> 19:08.335
so I could eat, drink, and relax
with the people I like.

19:10.379 --> 19:12.214
You're not allowed to come here anymore.

19:20.264 --> 19:21.223
Let's go.

19:25.060 --> 19:26.061
You see,

19:27.729 --> 19:29.106
I'm getting old now.

19:30.399 --> 19:33.694
Listening to someone talk nonstop
scares me more than anything.

19:41.159 --> 19:41.994
Goodbye.

19:43.328 --> 19:44.204
It's been…

19:45.372 --> 19:46.873
Well, I can't say it's been fun.

19:47.874 --> 19:48.709
Just take care.

19:51.211 --> 19:52.129
See you tomorrow.

20:26.204 --> 20:27.122
Don't come back here.

20:30.167 --> 20:33.170
HWANG DONG-MAN NOT ALLOWED

21:06.286 --> 21:07.496
I mean it.

21:08.872 --> 21:10.791
If Hwang Dong-man shows up, kick him out.

21:17.464 --> 21:20.092
HWANG JIN-CHEOL, LEE SUN-OK

21:49.871 --> 21:52.416
The wedding will be
on the 9th of next month.

21:54.167 --> 21:55.544
It's nice to meet you.

21:57.421 --> 21:59.131
He's the older brother,
and he's the younger one.

21:59.214 --> 22:00.966
I've heard a lot about you.

22:01.049 --> 22:02.634
You're a filmmaker, right?

22:03.301 --> 22:04.136
Yes.

22:05.011 --> 22:06.638
You don't need much in a man.

22:07.764 --> 22:09.266
As long as he stays grounded,

22:09.850 --> 22:11.977
has the grit to provide for his family,

22:12.060 --> 22:13.645
and works hard,

22:13.728 --> 22:14.980
that's enough.

22:15.814 --> 22:18.358
Back in the day, you couldn't be buried
in the family cemetery

22:18.442 --> 22:19.651
if you weren't married.

22:19.734 --> 22:21.361
You had to get married, have kids,

22:21.987 --> 22:26.032
and work hard to take care of your family

22:26.658 --> 22:28.410
to earn a place there.

22:29.453 --> 22:30.620
So, how did it go?

22:31.204 --> 22:32.747
-Did you look into it?
-Sorry?

22:33.248 --> 22:36.501
Did you find a celebrity
to sing at Ye-rin's wedding?

22:37.878 --> 22:39.087
You still haven't found one?

22:39.171 --> 22:40.672
I asked you about this ages ago.

22:41.923 --> 22:44.759
You can't do anything.
Look into it right away!

22:45.302 --> 22:47.095
If an elder tells you to do something,
you do it immediately!

22:47.179 --> 22:48.972
Why are you so slow?

22:51.600 --> 22:53.310
He can't book a celebrity for you.

22:53.810 --> 22:54.728
Ask someone else.

22:55.437 --> 22:57.105
He's been in that industry for 20 years.

22:57.814 --> 22:59.441
He doesn't have a close celebrity friend?

22:59.524 --> 23:01.067
No, he doesn't.

23:11.119 --> 23:13.663
-Let's take a photo together.
-I'll take it, ma'am.

23:13.747 --> 23:14.748
Why don't you all stand here?

23:15.373 --> 23:17.542
-You should be in it too.
-It's okay.

23:17.626 --> 23:18.543
-Take it vertically.
-Okay.

23:18.627 --> 23:20.253
-One, two, three.
-Here we go.

23:20.754 --> 23:22.130
You ladies aren't angry, are you?

23:22.756 --> 23:23.715
Here we go.

23:23.798 --> 23:25.133
-One, two, three.
-One, two, three.

23:25.759 --> 23:26.760
All done.

23:27.344 --> 23:30.472
When there's no welding work,
I harvest napa cabbage in Daegwallyeong.

23:30.555 --> 23:34.059
I work hard and only take
three or four days off a month.

23:34.142 --> 23:37.103
I'm saying Dong-man and I aren't poor
because we're lazy,

23:37.604 --> 23:40.899
just as you didn't become rich
from working hard.

23:42.776 --> 23:44.694
Just admit that you got lucky.

23:46.655 --> 23:49.824
You were lucky to have a man as selfless
as my father as your brother-in-law.

23:49.908 --> 23:53.703
That's the only reason you were able
to take all the Hwang family's fortune.

23:53.787 --> 23:56.206
Just know that I honored
my father's wishes

23:56.748 --> 24:00.168
and refused to get caught up
in a messy inheritance fight,

24:00.252 --> 24:05.632
which is why I live with the pride
of knowing I'm morally superior to you.

24:06.508 --> 24:09.469
At least I came out
with a sense of moral superiority.

24:09.552 --> 24:13.473
But Dong-man just did as I said
because he's got a good heart.

24:14.724 --> 24:17.852
What I'm saying is
you were able to take the family fortune,

24:18.353 --> 24:20.772
thanks to your proud nephew
and your good-hearted one.

24:20.855 --> 24:23.566
Not because you're so diligent
and hardworking!

24:29.072 --> 24:31.449
From now on, don't come
to our grandparents' memorial rites.

25:04.566 --> 25:08.445
The men in the Hwang family
have always been weak.

25:25.545 --> 25:27.172
You spineless bastard.

25:28.590 --> 25:30.925
Why do we have to help
with his damn daughter's wedding?

25:31.509 --> 25:34.554
You really think he asked without knowing
you couldn't pull that off?

25:35.138 --> 25:37.557
He knew but kept pushing
to get what he wanted

25:37.640 --> 25:38.725
because you're a fool!

25:38.808 --> 25:41.519
He knows you'll do anything
if he berates you enough!

25:43.521 --> 25:45.648
You're what they call a pushover, idiot.

25:46.274 --> 25:47.859
You should be swearing at him,

25:47.942 --> 25:50.153
not taking his calls like a dumbass!

25:53.865 --> 25:54.991
Then what?

25:56.076 --> 25:59.579
Should I have said, "I'm incompetent,
so I don't know a single celebrity"?

26:00.789 --> 26:02.165
"I've been in this industry

26:03.541 --> 26:05.502
for 20 years, but I have no influence"?

26:45.875 --> 26:48.294
How can you tell
if the world has ended or not?

26:50.380 --> 26:52.257
It comes down to the weather.

26:54.676 --> 26:56.761
As long as there are clouds in the sky,

26:56.845 --> 26:58.179
wind in the air,

26:58.847 --> 27:00.640
and leaves stirring in the breeze…

27:02.308 --> 27:03.518
As long as weather exists…

27:06.146 --> 27:07.814
the world hasn't ended.

27:16.156 --> 27:19.492
Actor Song's agency called
and asked that we wait a bit longer.

27:19.576 --> 27:21.286
The film they're shooting
has been delayed,

27:21.369 --> 27:23.955
so they haven't had a chance to read it.

27:24.038 --> 27:28.042
Actor Byeon will finish filming this week,
so they'll get back to us by next week.

27:28.626 --> 27:29.919
Is waiting around your job?

27:30.545 --> 27:34.215
You waited last week
and the week before that.

27:34.299 --> 27:37.844
All you've been reporting to me this month
is that you're waiting.

27:39.637 --> 27:42.640
Actor Song doesn't read
other screenplays while filming,

27:42.724 --> 27:44.267
-so as soon as it's over--
-Hey.

27:44.851 --> 27:47.020
Actor Song has a meeting
at Agit today, right?

27:47.520 --> 27:49.522
Yeah. At what time?

27:50.732 --> 27:51.816
Okay, got it.

27:51.900 --> 27:54.319
Don't tell them I'm coming.
Just act like you don't know.

27:55.028 --> 27:55.945
Okay.

27:59.491 --> 28:00.909
Go print out the screenplay.

28:05.830 --> 28:07.749
I said go and print it out!

28:33.024 --> 28:35.109
I wish Mr. Choi

28:35.985 --> 28:39.322
wouldn't treat Eun-a like that
in front of all of us.

28:39.405 --> 28:41.824
It makes me feel like an accomplice,

28:42.492 --> 28:43.326
and I feel bad.

28:44.118 --> 28:46.913
I feel for her,
but she has to handle it on her own.

28:47.497 --> 28:49.165
He doted on her for a while, didn't he?

28:49.249 --> 28:50.250
What happened?

28:50.959 --> 28:52.335
When she started,

28:52.418 --> 28:55.755
she tore into screenplays
with an unbiased perspective.

28:55.839 --> 28:57.257
It was new.

28:57.340 --> 29:01.261
After years of hearing the same clichés
about authenticity and whatnot,

29:01.344 --> 29:03.137
I'm sure Mr. Choi was impressed.

29:03.763 --> 29:07.225
The way Eun-a talks
is raw and instinctive, you know?

29:07.308 --> 29:08.852
And she has those sudden outbursts.

29:09.769 --> 29:12.063
But after a year,

29:12.146 --> 29:13.940
I guess that appeal wore off.

29:15.650 --> 29:17.402
It's like a relationship.

29:17.485 --> 29:19.112
Everything in the first year shines,

29:19.195 --> 29:21.489
with ways of speaking and humor
that are completely new to you.

29:22.156 --> 29:24.576
But after a year, not so much.

29:25.118 --> 29:26.286
That's just how it is.

29:27.787 --> 29:31.875
It's just scary to see someone
fold under like that.

29:33.167 --> 29:35.545
She even stutters now.

29:35.628 --> 29:38.506
It goes to show how fragile people are.

29:38.590 --> 29:40.800
One glance can send them
to heaven or hell.

30:10.830 --> 30:11.998
HANKUK UNIVERSITY HOSPITAL

30:12.081 --> 30:13.166
As I said before,

30:13.750 --> 30:16.794
you're manifesting physical symptoms

30:16.878 --> 30:19.422
from the extreme stress
you're experiencing.

30:22.717 --> 30:25.678
What does the emotion watch say
when you get nosebleeds?

30:35.438 --> 30:36.940
UNKNOWN

30:37.023 --> 30:38.691
Aside from "unknown,"

30:38.775 --> 30:41.527
do any other words appear
when you get nosebleeds?

30:44.530 --> 30:45.448
No.

30:49.535 --> 30:52.580
We need to gather opinions from people
with the same pattern,

30:53.206 --> 30:56.084
and decide what to call this emotion.

30:57.126 --> 30:59.671
But no one else has shown
this type of pattern yet.

31:00.380 --> 31:04.717
Anger, despair, and sadness
make up about 90% of this emotion,

31:05.843 --> 31:08.346
along with a bit of desperation.

31:09.347 --> 31:11.849
What do you think
we should call this emotion?

31:14.769 --> 31:17.230
Can you think back
to how you felt at the time?

31:43.506 --> 31:44.382
Self-destructive.

31:48.803 --> 31:50.388
Like I wanted to self-destruct.

32:13.411 --> 32:14.579
When I was nine.

32:17.540 --> 32:19.250
I was in the second grade.

32:21.085 --> 32:24.964
Even back then,
I'd get nosebleeds in similar situations.

32:26.174 --> 32:28.593
When I felt all alone

32:29.385 --> 32:30.470
and hopeless.

32:32.096 --> 32:33.639
When I was young, I felt hopeless…

32:36.559 --> 32:38.519
and I couldn't breathe.

32:41.647 --> 32:43.274
I still feel the same way,

32:44.859 --> 32:47.361
but now there's an additional feeling.

32:49.405 --> 32:51.074
The feeling of having witnessed

32:52.241 --> 32:53.534
their weakness.

33:15.223 --> 33:17.433
Hey, Hwang! Let's grab some lunch!

33:43.376 --> 33:46.629
DONG-MAN

34:12.655 --> 34:15.825
HWANG DONG-MAN NOT ALLOWED

34:19.829 --> 34:20.955
Welcome.

34:25.251 --> 34:26.377
Hello.

34:30.965 --> 34:33.092
-What can I get you?
-Anything will do.

34:35.678 --> 34:36.637
Who is that?

34:36.721 --> 34:38.639
Dong-man's older brother.

34:44.645 --> 34:45.563
Here you go, sir.

34:56.032 --> 34:57.867
How many degrees is the Earth tilted?

35:02.121 --> 35:02.955
Well?

35:05.208 --> 35:06.417
It's tilted, right?

35:08.461 --> 35:09.962
By 23.5 degrees.

35:11.297 --> 35:13.090
By 23.5 degrees, huh?

35:15.551 --> 35:17.386
The Earth is tilted by 23.5 degrees,

35:17.470 --> 35:19.972
and it produces
9.6 billion tons of food per year.

35:20.598 --> 35:22.391
The global population is 7.7 billion.

35:22.475 --> 35:24.977
Even if each person ate a ton a year,
there'd still be food left over.

35:25.061 --> 35:28.314
All you have to do is sit back
and eat whatever the Earth provides.

35:28.397 --> 35:31.025
Instead, you fill your head with bullshit
about making movies

35:31.108 --> 35:33.319
and go on and on about them.

35:33.986 --> 35:35.154
Such important work, huh?

35:37.657 --> 35:40.326
No one would say anything
if he'd just stop doing crazy things.

35:40.409 --> 35:42.328
He goes around causing trouble

35:42.995 --> 35:44.372
and trying to ruin everything.

35:45.248 --> 35:48.876
Are you bunch so weak that
Hwang Dong-man can ruin you if he tried?

35:49.752 --> 35:50.628
Tell me.

35:50.711 --> 35:52.588
Is Hwang Dong-man really that powerful?

35:53.214 --> 35:54.048
I had no idea.

35:55.591 --> 35:57.009
He's not my son,

35:57.093 --> 36:00.263
but if seeing my 40-year-old brother
get bullied sets me off like this,

36:01.305 --> 36:02.974
I'd go homicidal if he were.

36:06.560 --> 36:10.022
This is the kind of bullying you see
in elementary school, you assholes.

36:10.106 --> 36:13.734
Adults call it cutting ties, not bullying.

36:13.818 --> 36:15.987
Cutting ties as a group
is called bullying, you bastard!

36:16.070 --> 36:18.864
Putting up signs like that
for everyone to see is bullying!

36:18.948 --> 36:20.950
Do you realize
how big a moron your brother is

36:21.033 --> 36:23.828
to make grown-ass adults act like this?

36:25.204 --> 36:28.124
Actually, "moron" sounds too adorable.
Got anything better?

36:28.207 --> 36:30.459
Give me a second.
I'm thinking hard right now.

36:30.543 --> 36:32.420
-Calm down, please.
-Think faster.

36:32.503 --> 36:36.590
An attention-seeking loud-ass
trying to hide how worthless he is

36:36.674 --> 36:39.176
and a complete idiot trying to
convince himself that his shitty situation

36:39.260 --> 36:40.469
-is actually--
-Jin-man!

36:41.971 --> 36:43.431
You piece of shit.

36:43.514 --> 36:45.599
-Hey, get him out of here.
-Let go of me.

36:45.683 --> 36:46.892
Let go of me, punk!

36:48.144 --> 36:49.145
Sorry about that.

36:49.937 --> 36:51.439
-I'm sorry.
-Goddamn it.

36:52.606 --> 36:53.941
What the hell was that?

36:56.485 --> 36:58.696
People like them are making movies?

36:58.779 --> 36:59.739
Hey!

36:59.822 --> 37:01.782
Try being decent human beings first,
you assholes!

37:02.366 --> 37:03.743
No, Jin-man. Just let it go.

37:03.826 --> 37:05.244
-Let go. My bag…
-Please.

37:05.328 --> 37:07.663
I need to go back for my bag!

37:07.747 --> 37:08.706
Let go!

37:23.846 --> 37:25.973
HWANG DONG-MAN AND HIS BROTHER
NOT ALLOWED

37:28.476 --> 37:29.310
Go ahead.

37:30.686 --> 37:32.521
Pick on the brothers!

37:34.815 --> 37:37.151
Dong-man isn't alone in this!

37:40.404 --> 37:43.991
Forget making movies.
Just pack up and come with me, you idiot.

37:44.075 --> 37:45.951
You're 40, not 12.

37:46.035 --> 37:47.995
Why would you get bullied
in your own neighborhood?

37:48.579 --> 37:50.206
I'm not getting bullied!

37:50.289 --> 37:51.999
It was just a little fight!

37:52.083 --> 37:54.794
They admitted they were bullying you!

37:54.877 --> 37:57.338
If you have any pride left,
just leave the industry!

38:00.466 --> 38:01.300
Did you get beaten up?

38:01.384 --> 38:03.552
Of course not!

38:03.636 --> 38:04.595
Then how did you get hurt?

38:04.678 --> 38:06.222
I didn't get hurt!

38:06.305 --> 38:07.765
Then what's with the cast?

38:07.848 --> 38:09.058
This is just…

38:09.642 --> 38:12.645
It's just a joke, okay?

38:13.479 --> 38:15.439
I didn't get hurt!

38:15.940 --> 38:19.151
-Then why the hell do you have a cast on?
-No reason! I just put it on!

38:20.569 --> 38:22.029
You little bastard.

38:22.947 --> 38:24.031
What are you doing?

38:24.615 --> 38:25.950
What are you, a damn kid?

38:26.033 --> 38:28.577
Get your shit together
before I throw you into a mental hospital!

38:28.661 --> 38:30.621
Why would I go to a mental hospital?

38:32.081 --> 38:33.124
What do you even want?

38:34.542 --> 38:36.127
To debut? To be successful?

38:36.627 --> 38:37.503
What is it?

38:39.255 --> 38:40.673
Just tell me, and I'll help you!

38:40.756 --> 38:42.049
What is it?

38:42.133 --> 38:43.175
Success?

38:43.968 --> 38:44.969
I never said that.

38:45.594 --> 38:46.637
Then what is it?

38:51.183 --> 38:52.601
To not feel anxious.

38:56.355 --> 38:57.189
All I want…

38:58.482 --> 39:00.109
is to not feel anxious.

39:26.385 --> 39:27.553
Find yourself a woman.

39:29.513 --> 39:32.808
You're not brave enough
to grow old and die on your own.

39:33.434 --> 39:35.019
That's just who you are.

39:35.102 --> 39:36.729
You're materialistic

39:37.521 --> 39:39.231
and family-oriented.

39:40.900 --> 39:41.901
So find a woman.

40:10.888 --> 40:12.598
Okay. Give me a minute.

40:28.489 --> 40:29.532
Let's go.

40:35.120 --> 40:38.040
Things are good for at least a month
after a big blow-up.

40:56.517 --> 40:57.893
Oh my gosh. No way.

40:59.144 --> 40:59.979
What is it?

41:00.062 --> 41:02.523
The sign now says "Hwang Dong-man
and his brother not allowed."

41:02.606 --> 41:03.899
No way.

41:04.483 --> 41:07.903
Apparently, his older brother
stopped by and caused a scene.

41:07.987 --> 41:09.613
Those brothers are really something.

41:09.697 --> 41:10.823
Isn't Hye-jin amazing?

41:11.907 --> 41:13.742
She solved the problem with a single sign,

41:13.826 --> 41:16.745
so no one else
had to get their hands dirty.

41:16.829 --> 41:18.038
I know, right?

41:18.122 --> 41:19.456
I can finally relax now.

41:19.540 --> 41:22.251
The thought of not seeing Hwang Dong-man
at Agit makes me so happy.

41:24.712 --> 41:27.381
Why do you all find Director Hwang
so hard to deal with?

41:30.009 --> 41:31.010
You should see for yourself.

41:31.635 --> 41:34.096
To put it simply, he's incompetent.

41:34.179 --> 41:35.598
Being incompetent is fine,

41:35.681 --> 41:38.684
but people who try to cover that up
by talking nonstop

41:38.767 --> 41:40.019
are the absolute worst.

41:41.270 --> 41:42.646
What do you mean by incompetent?

41:45.691 --> 41:47.693
You're a chef, but you can't cook.

41:48.319 --> 41:50.154
You're a teacher, but you can't teach.

41:50.904 --> 41:52.031
Should I continue?

41:52.531 --> 41:54.950
You're human, but you're not humane.

41:57.161 --> 41:58.704
Isn't that peak incompetence?

42:03.167 --> 42:04.001
Seriously?

42:05.127 --> 42:07.212
Are you saying Hwang Dong-man is humane?

42:07.296 --> 42:10.424
And you're saying that we aren't.

42:14.511 --> 42:16.847
So being incompetent makes you humane,

42:16.930 --> 42:18.641
but being competent doesn't?

42:20.934 --> 42:23.062
She said Hwang Dong-man is humane.

42:24.730 --> 42:26.940
I've never heard the word "humane"

42:27.024 --> 42:29.777
sound so damn stupid.

42:31.904 --> 42:33.739
I'd rather be inhumane, then.

42:42.289 --> 42:43.457
Oh, my chest.

42:46.752 --> 42:47.920
Here's to the share hitting 200,000!

42:48.003 --> 42:49.421
-Cheers!
-Cheers!

42:53.592 --> 42:54.843
Just a little while ago,

42:56.345 --> 42:58.847
I was fired up to get revenge on Mr. Choi.

42:58.931 --> 43:01.350
-Can we get another bottle of soju?
-One second, please.

43:05.145 --> 43:07.439
I lose my willpower when I'm full.

43:08.023 --> 43:09.191
I have to stay hungry

43:10.317 --> 43:11.777
to be as quick as a wild dog.

43:14.321 --> 43:15.739
-Here's your steamed eggs.
-Thank you.

43:15.823 --> 43:17.491
-Enjoy.
-This looks so good.

43:17.574 --> 43:18.659
Steamed eggs.

43:20.786 --> 43:23.789
JEONG KOREAN BBQ

43:28.293 --> 43:30.212
What happened to your arm?

43:34.299 --> 43:35.843
I got a call from Mr. Choi.

43:37.886 --> 43:40.055
I sent Eun-a my screenplay, you see.

43:42.433 --> 43:44.518
I went there full of hope, but…

43:49.773 --> 43:52.276
I've never heard anything
so hurtful in my life.

43:55.946 --> 43:58.532
My heart started pounding like crazy.

43:59.533 --> 44:01.118
Even more than "unemployed."

44:01.201 --> 44:04.037
And this watch kept vibrating.

44:06.415 --> 44:07.583
What did it say?

44:09.376 --> 44:10.377
"Deeply humiliated"?

44:16.550 --> 44:17.885
HUNGRY

44:17.968 --> 44:21.096
It was scarier than deep humiliation.

44:23.640 --> 44:27.561
It felt like a UFC heavyweight champion
had kicked my ass in the third round.

44:27.644 --> 44:30.773
It hurt so much
that I thought I'd broken some bones.

44:31.523 --> 44:34.443
I felt like I had to
wrap myself up to cope,

44:34.526 --> 44:37.821
so I woke up crying
in the middle of the night

44:37.905 --> 44:41.325
and wrapped myself as tightly as I could.

44:42.367 --> 44:44.411
Only then did it feel like
it didn't hurt as much.

44:48.207 --> 44:49.208
But nope.

44:49.958 --> 44:51.335
I'm not fully healed yet.

44:52.002 --> 44:53.295
It'll take some time to heal.

44:55.255 --> 44:57.257
You know how bones get stronger
after being in a cast?

44:57.966 --> 44:58.926
Just wait.

44:59.009 --> 45:02.679
My confidence, pride,
mental strength, and willpower

45:03.430 --> 45:04.723
will come back way stronger.

45:04.806 --> 45:06.475
They'll never break again.

45:10.771 --> 45:11.605
Hey.

45:13.565 --> 45:17.903
Why are you looking at me so lovingly?

45:18.862 --> 45:19.821
Have you fallen for me?

45:22.366 --> 45:24.117
Jeez, seriously.

45:26.286 --> 45:27.120
I mean,

45:27.871 --> 45:29.248
I wouldn't be surprised if you did.

45:31.625 --> 45:34.002
I don't have any hard feelings
toward Eun-a.

45:34.086 --> 45:37.422
Mr. Choi caught her reading it
because I'd asked her to take a look.

45:38.048 --> 45:41.552
If Eun-a were still in her prime
and had ripped into you,

45:42.594 --> 45:44.263
you wouldn't even be alive.

45:44.346 --> 45:46.848
It amazed me how she'd
tear a screenplay apart without malice.

45:47.474 --> 45:48.809
I once saw Yeong-su look so blank

45:49.434 --> 45:52.437
after Eun-a tore into him,
like his face had disappeared.

45:53.313 --> 45:55.816
He was completely dazed

45:55.899 --> 45:57.442
that his features just vanished.

45:58.068 --> 45:59.528
She ripped into me once too,

45:59.611 --> 46:01.947
but that harsh feedback moved me to tears.

46:02.030 --> 46:04.866
-Come on.
-It was sharp and to the point.

46:04.950 --> 46:07.286
I wanted to gather up
what was left of my brain

46:07.369 --> 46:09.121
-Yeah?
-and beg her, "Tear it apart!"

46:09.705 --> 46:11.373
"Tear it apart!"

46:11.456 --> 46:14.167
I wanted to ask her to go at me again.

46:14.251 --> 46:17.963
You know those stubborn directors
who refuse to make revisions?

46:18.046 --> 46:21.675
Mr. Choi sent Eun-a to the front lines
to tear them apart in his place.

46:21.758 --> 46:25.971
But later, all those directors lined up
wanting to get torn to shreds by her.

46:26.471 --> 46:30.100
When she entered the room,
everyone's eyes lit up.

46:31.101 --> 46:33.895
It made me think,
"So this is what it means to truly shine."

46:33.979 --> 46:35.647
-Come on.
-I'm serious!

46:36.273 --> 46:38.442
Whenever she showed up,

46:39.026 --> 46:41.361
the room would light up,
like someone had flipped a switch.

46:46.241 --> 46:48.327
That's how sharp she used to be.

46:51.371 --> 46:54.207
I like the current Eun-a

46:54.291 --> 46:55.959
better than the sharp Eun-a.

46:57.502 --> 46:58.545
Back then,

46:59.838 --> 47:01.923
she was too…

47:03.050 --> 47:03.884
too intense.

47:04.509 --> 47:05.344
It was uncomfortable.

47:06.928 --> 47:08.263
So why'd she change all of a sudden?

47:08.805 --> 47:09.848
Like she's sick or something.

47:10.432 --> 47:11.391
I don't know.

47:12.142 --> 47:14.645
I don't think she gets along
with anyone at work either.

47:15.228 --> 47:16.188
Why not?

47:16.271 --> 47:19.274
I mean, all the directors
skip Mr. Choi and Hyo-jin.

47:19.358 --> 47:20.942
-If you look at the back…
-They just send

47:21.026 --> 47:23.320
their screenplays
straight to Eun-a for review.

47:25.322 --> 47:26.573
I guess that upsets them.

47:31.036 --> 47:32.371
-How about one more drink?
-What?

47:32.454 --> 47:34.373
-Just one more.
-Forget it. I'm tired.

47:34.456 --> 47:35.499
Go home already.

48:06.405 --> 48:08.448
How do people gain power?

48:12.619 --> 48:15.122
Like a hyena searching for prey
at the foot of a mountain,

48:15.872 --> 48:17.249
I went searching for power.

48:18.834 --> 48:20.836
But I failed, so I'm heading home

48:21.878 --> 48:22.838
right now.

48:24.840 --> 48:26.216
After eating a ton of meat, that is.

48:32.806 --> 48:34.015
Do you happen to know

48:35.016 --> 48:36.852
where they sell power?

48:39.312 --> 48:40.355
I'd like to buy some.

48:50.741 --> 48:52.409
Maybe if you love someone…

48:57.789 --> 48:59.040
What if the protagonist…

49:01.042 --> 49:05.130
was driven by his love for his niece
or nephew who wants to see the weather?

49:06.548 --> 49:07.424
Or maybe

49:08.300 --> 49:09.926
for his beloved older brother?

49:13.555 --> 49:15.807
Then his heart would race,

49:16.516 --> 49:18.268
because he'd do anything
to make it happen.

49:24.983 --> 49:27.152
I realized something
as I read your screenplay.

49:29.279 --> 49:30.363
"Oh…

49:31.865 --> 49:33.950
This director has nothing…

49:36.620 --> 49:37.913
that he loves."

50:28.296 --> 50:29.631
I'm home.

50:31.299 --> 50:32.175
Come on in.

50:35.512 --> 50:37.430
Did he eat it all and not waste anything?

50:38.014 --> 50:38.849
Yes.

50:50.485 --> 50:51.653
Being in love

50:52.362 --> 50:53.655
made everything easy.

50:55.365 --> 50:57.117
But when it ended,

50:58.243 --> 51:01.329
I realized that things I'd forgotten,
and thought were gone,

51:02.873 --> 51:04.207
was still there.

51:06.918 --> 51:08.503
It never left.

51:10.589 --> 51:12.299
This crippling lethargy.

51:27.272 --> 51:28.148
Relax your eyes.

51:36.781 --> 51:37.616
Your eyes.

51:45.415 --> 51:47.083
He's a nobody.

51:47.167 --> 51:49.419
How dare he act like
we're in the same league?

51:51.880 --> 51:53.381
He is in the same league.

51:54.674 --> 51:57.177
You made some movies, and Dong-man didn't.

51:57.260 --> 51:58.553
That's the only difference.

52:00.138 --> 52:01.932
Who's to say he'll never make a movie?

52:02.015 --> 52:03.642
He won't. Ever.

52:05.310 --> 52:07.646
-What if I help him debut?
-Are you crazy?

52:11.024 --> 52:13.944
Why don't you try being a little nicer,
Director Park Gyeong-se?

52:15.153 --> 52:17.864
If you hadn't debuted yet,
would you have acted any differently?

52:18.907 --> 52:22.035
You think you'd have accepted your failure
and lived quietly?

52:22.118 --> 52:23.036
Don't kid yourself.

52:23.662 --> 52:26.456
You would've lost your shit
even worse than Hwang Dong-man.

52:27.082 --> 52:30.460
I knew you would, so I did everything
I could to make sure you debuted.

52:30.543 --> 52:32.379
So I'd never have to
see you hit rock bottom.

52:33.922 --> 52:35.674
How could you say something so harsh?

52:36.383 --> 52:37.842
I'm not done yet!

52:43.556 --> 52:45.976
If you want to be different from him,

52:46.476 --> 52:48.228
then prove that you're different.

52:49.479 --> 52:51.648
You're pitching a fit
because you're just the same.

52:53.024 --> 52:57.153
If he did that to Director Bong Joon-ho,
would he have had a meltdown like you?

52:57.237 --> 52:58.488
No, he'd laugh it off.

52:59.197 --> 53:01.282
If you're truly
on a whole different level,

53:01.366 --> 53:03.368
you have to prove it yourself,

53:03.994 --> 53:07.789
instead of whining and bitching
about how different you two are.

53:46.828 --> 53:48.288
Hey, Dong-man!

53:48.371 --> 53:50.206
Hwang Dong-man!

53:52.917 --> 53:55.503
Hey, you bastard! I'm trying to sleep!

53:56.254 --> 53:57.338
I'm here!

53:59.090 --> 54:00.425
I'm here!

54:02.052 --> 54:03.303
Hey, Dong-man!

54:06.389 --> 54:07.599
Hwang Dong-man!

54:20.111 --> 54:21.654
When I was young, I felt hopeless…

54:22.781 --> 54:24.532
and I couldn't breathe.

54:25.867 --> 54:27.577
I still feel the same way,

54:28.953 --> 54:31.623
but now there's an additional feeling.

54:33.583 --> 54:35.043
The feeling of having witnessed

54:36.044 --> 54:37.170
their weakness.

54:39.214 --> 54:40.256
And that…

54:41.925 --> 54:43.885
makes me feel like I could fight them.

55:03.071 --> 55:05.156
Mr. Choi Dong-hyeon, are you in there?

55:10.954 --> 55:12.539
DIRECTOR'S ROOM 4

55:13.123 --> 55:14.332
Hwang Dong-man is here.

55:15.333 --> 55:16.376
Hwang Dong-man is here.

55:25.844 --> 55:27.846
It's okay. Let him stay.

55:33.184 --> 55:36.896
You divide people into classes,
keeping the successful, shiny ones close,

55:36.980 --> 55:39.732
while treating losers like me
as if we've got some contagious disease

55:39.816 --> 55:43.111
and trying to shove us aside.

55:43.903 --> 55:46.781
Go ahead and try building a shiny world
with just the shiny people.

55:46.865 --> 55:47.907
It won't shine at all.

55:48.908 --> 55:51.828
By the way, I'm freaking good at
talking behind people's backs.

55:51.911 --> 55:53.913
I told you to stop saying
words like "freaking," you bastard.

55:53.997 --> 55:55.748
Stop calling me "bastard"!

55:56.457 --> 55:58.376
And don't interrupt me.

55:58.459 --> 56:00.461
I'm normally freaking talkative,

56:00.545 --> 56:02.505
but I held my tongue and listened to you.

56:03.590 --> 56:04.883
So now it's your turn to listen.

56:04.966 --> 56:06.885
That's showing respect in a conversation!

56:07.468 --> 56:08.303
Okay.

56:09.804 --> 56:11.514
Go ahead, I'll listen.

56:15.852 --> 56:17.312
Damn it, I forgot.

56:22.358 --> 56:24.194
Let me start over.

56:24.277 --> 56:25.320
Listen carefully.

56:26.946 --> 56:27.780
Ready.

56:29.115 --> 56:29.949
Action.

56:30.033 --> 56:32.911
Do you know why so many murders occur?

56:34.329 --> 56:36.247
Disrespect. Complete disrespect.

56:36.331 --> 56:39.292
The only reason you didn't die that day
is because I'm a saint.

56:39.375 --> 56:41.586
I'm freaking good at
talking behind people's backs.

56:41.669 --> 56:42.670
But do you know why

56:43.254 --> 56:45.340
I never do it to someone's face?

56:45.423 --> 56:46.841
Because it's the polite thing to do.

56:47.425 --> 56:48.676
Then I saw you and realized

56:48.760 --> 56:52.096
that people in this industry think
saying things to someone's face

56:52.180 --> 56:53.640
gives them power.

56:53.723 --> 56:55.183
They think calling a loser a loser

56:55.266 --> 56:57.560
is some brilliant insight
they came up with themselves.

56:57.644 --> 56:59.437
They think being a rude-ass
gives them power.

56:59.520 --> 57:00.647
If that's the case,

57:00.730 --> 57:01.898
I'll say it to your face too.

57:03.191 --> 57:04.776
I'm done talking behind people's backs.

57:04.859 --> 57:06.653
I'll just say it in front of everybody.

57:07.320 --> 57:08.529
All of you.

57:09.030 --> 57:10.657
I'll say it to your faces.

57:10.740 --> 57:11.950
Look forward to it.

57:16.663 --> 57:19.290
Here's what I came to tell
Choi Dong-hyeon to his face.

57:19.874 --> 57:21.960
Don't act like you're the adult here.

57:22.043 --> 57:24.170
Nobody here asked you to.

57:24.254 --> 57:26.756
And stop sending your innocent juniors
to the front lines

57:26.839 --> 57:29.968
to take shots at directors
who don't listen to you.

57:30.718 --> 57:32.178
What are they, cannon fodder?

57:33.471 --> 57:34.722
And just you wait.

57:34.806 --> 57:37.058
I'm about to become something incredible.

57:37.141 --> 57:38.393
I'm going to become incredibly

57:38.476 --> 57:40.687
and even more, more, more, more worthless,

57:40.770 --> 57:43.398
and even more, more, more, more useless.

57:43.481 --> 57:47.485
And I'm going to piss you all off
more and more and more and more!

57:48.486 --> 57:49.487
Brace yourselves.

57:50.321 --> 57:51.656
You'll end up waving a white flag.

57:53.116 --> 57:54.075
And finally!

57:58.329 --> 57:59.956
I'm going to pull up the shiny truth…

58:03.001 --> 58:05.211
from the very depths of my worthlessness.

58:07.338 --> 58:09.382
Look forward to my shiny story.

58:12.010 --> 58:13.094
Stop me if you can.

58:13.720 --> 58:14.804
I dare you to.

58:20.435 --> 58:21.269
Hang on.

58:22.103 --> 58:23.438
It's my turn to talk.

58:23.521 --> 58:24.564
No thanks, I'm busy.

58:26.816 --> 58:29.402
Has he been day drinking or what?

58:31.946 --> 58:33.031
Did you just laugh?

58:34.324 --> 58:37.160
Look at you, all cheerful and smiling.

58:37.994 --> 58:38.995
That's a first.

58:59.182 --> 59:00.016
Cut.

59:02.477 --> 59:03.895
I just fell in love with myself.

59:04.520 --> 59:06.356
I love this guy.

59:07.190 --> 59:09.067
I think I can even have sex with myself.

59:10.151 --> 59:11.152
What should I do?

59:12.320 --> 59:13.488
This guy is so cool.

59:25.833 --> 59:28.961
Every day is just spectacular
thanks to Hwang Dong-man…

59:31.214 --> 59:32.924
I can't talk. My lungs hurt too much.

59:33.549 --> 59:34.509
What's wrong?

59:34.592 --> 59:38.721
I started choking when I was talking shit
about Hwang Dong-man yesterday.

59:40.765 --> 59:44.352
I thought I was going to die
and almost called 911.

59:53.361 --> 59:56.239
When I get nosebleeds from stress…

59:58.533 --> 01:00:00.493
It's my body telling me
I'm killing myself.

01:00:02.203 --> 01:00:03.246
It shows

01:00:04.122 --> 01:00:05.665
how powerful the mind is.

01:00:06.457 --> 01:00:07.583
I understand that much.

01:00:08.334 --> 01:00:09.210
But…

01:00:11.504 --> 01:00:13.798
is it possible to go from hurting myself…

01:00:16.843 --> 01:00:20.847
to hurting someone else?

01:00:20.930 --> 01:00:22.974
She said Hwang Dong-man is humane.

01:00:24.809 --> 01:00:26.769
I've never heard the word "humane"

01:00:26.853 --> 01:00:29.647
sound so damn stupid.

01:00:31.774 --> 01:00:33.568
I'd rather be inhumane, then.

01:00:38.990 --> 01:00:39.949
Oh, my chest.

01:00:44.078 --> 01:00:46.539
…and productively from now on.

01:01:00.553 --> 01:01:02.096
You crazy bastard! What are you doing?

01:01:06.809 --> 01:01:07.643
That day.

01:01:09.437 --> 01:01:13.775
I've been replaying that day in my head,
down to every tenth of a second.

01:01:16.235 --> 01:01:19.363
And I'm positive Hwang Dong-man
never even brushed against me.

01:01:21.657 --> 01:01:22.492
But…

01:01:25.203 --> 01:01:26.579
it was strange.

01:01:30.124 --> 01:01:31.334
You know what?

01:01:32.710 --> 01:01:34.253
He must be possessed.

01:02:04.659 --> 01:02:05.701
They're side dishes.

01:02:06.744 --> 01:02:07.787
My grandmother made them.

01:02:10.706 --> 01:02:11.582
You can have them.

01:02:33.271 --> 01:02:34.188
We're in sync.

01:02:51.747 --> 01:02:52.582
Thank you.

01:03:58.439 --> 01:03:59.273
You're…

01:04:01.484 --> 01:04:02.818
more beautiful than the weather.

01:04:15.331 --> 01:04:18.626
WE ARE ALL TRYING HERE

01:04:37.186 --> 01:04:38.104
Eun-a!

01:04:38.187 --> 01:04:39.855
When I'm with someone who likes me,

01:04:40.439 --> 01:04:41.857
I become really gentle.

01:04:41.941 --> 01:04:45.486
You seem like someone
with a thousand doors wide open.

01:04:46.988 --> 01:04:49.115
I'll see for myself
what Hwang Dong-man is like.

01:04:50.324 --> 01:04:52.618
Gyeong-se can never see this.

01:04:52.702 --> 01:04:53.536
Hwang Dong-man!

01:04:54.328 --> 01:04:56.831
You're just a nobody.

01:04:57.289 --> 01:04:58.666
Is it Hwang Dong-man this time?

01:04:59.166 --> 01:05:01.043
I wish you'd just die.

01:05:01.627 --> 01:05:03.796
Whenever I come across
a similar situation,

01:05:03.879 --> 01:05:06.215
I'm right back at that moment,

01:05:06.298 --> 01:05:07.633
paralyzed with fear.

01:05:08.217 --> 01:05:09.635
Who do you think it was?

01:05:09.719 --> 01:05:12.388
Who do you think was the first person
to cross you off?

01:05:12.972 --> 01:05:17.935
Subtitle translation by: Jenny Kim
